tp://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:19:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> If you are Spec'd to say 25 in Critical Strike you will get some amount of damage on Grays. Lets say 500 to make it a nice round number. People have said raising Critical Strike raises your max damage so if you get more points and put them into Critical Strike brining you up to 26 you now might do 510 damage.<br><br>Correct?<br><br>Repeat scenario but include level this time. If you are level 25 and do 500 Damage with your Critical Strike at 25, get Level 26, bump your Spec Level up to 26, and now you do 510 Damage. Both levels you are fully spec'd but at 26 you did more damage than at 25.<br><br>Correct?<br><br>Repeat scenario but this time don't put points into Critical Strike. You are level 25 and do 500 damage with Critical Strike at 25, get level 26, and now you do 500 damage with Critical Strike. You are now not fully spec'd but you do the same amount of damage you did at 25.<br><br>Correct?<br><br>Repeat scenario but this time exaggerate levels. You are level 25 and do 500 damage with Critical Strike at 25, you get level 26, 27, ... , 40, 41, 42 and you never put any more points into Critical Strike. You still do 500 damage. At level 50 you would be 50% spec'd and still do 500 damage. <br><br>Correct? <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukosmaul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kosmaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/gevry12/daoc/emblem WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> last few scenario's would only be valid if DPS on weapon didnt change. <br><br>I usally get damage increase as I level because I can use better DPS weps. <br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzadokbaccarat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zadok Baccarat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 4:18:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> 1) Correct<br><br>2)Correct but level of the character is immaterial. Character level has no effect on the upper cap of CS other than to validate that you can spec CS to your level. In other words, if a level 25 character with 25 CS spec (full spec) has a cap of 500 points, a level 50 character with a CS spec of 25 (50%) also has a cap of 500 points. (oops, I guess that's #4).<br><br>3) Correct. The amount you spec in CS determines the upper maximum, regardless of your character level.<br><br>4)Correct, see 2 above.<br><br><br>The important fact to remember is that each CS style is essentially a multiplier to the damage you've done with it. The base damage is determined by your level vs the target level, factor in your weapon skill, and then multiplied. At higher levels it's very very easy to hit that CS cap (especially vs grays) and thus you will see your CS attacks increase by 9 points for every CS point added. <p><br><TABLE bgColor=black border=0 cellPadding=0 cellSpacing=0 width=500> <TR><TD><IMG src="http://nemus.freewebspace.com/inf_sig.jpg"></TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 5:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> So why do the developers talk about 50% and 2/3 and full spec? <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udateeny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dateeny</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=u