Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> What I think it tells you is if you plan to stop midspec on a skill, do it as early as possible so you get the maximum benefit.  At 23 I have 21 in critical strike, and that will be the last or next last point I ever put into it, so I can enjoy Perf Artery to my heart's content.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 6:48:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> So your Pref Art will be 250 points lower than someone else when your both level 50? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 8:18:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/ciardha60a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So your Pref Art will be 250 points lower than someone else when your both level 50?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Assuming no item/rank bonuses, comparing 21 CS to 50 CS... 261 points lower maximum, yes.  The maximum cap seems to go up 9 points per level of CS spec, regardless of weapon.<br><br>Which I suppose means that the maximum damage cap is something like (DPS*Delay*something)+(CS*9). <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade of Guinevere<br><small>Explorer 93% | Killer 60% | Socializer 40% | Achiever 6%</small><br><i>"You killed a little dwarf.  You brute."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 9:12:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> something = 3 for 1-h weapons and staves in Hibernia.<br><br>Must be a base CS amount because I'm getting much higher PA numbers than CS*9. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A> at: 2/8/02 9:16:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uditherdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dither DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 11:41:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/dither/smiley2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> I'm starting to think theres a problem with testing vs greys.<br><br>Firstly, weapon condition and quality aren't getting factored in or something.  2 player crafted weapons of differing conditions and qualities hit for the same max, when according to the numbers given at the herald, an 89% qual weapon should hit for 89% of the damage a 100% qual weapon does, regardless of mob con.<br><br>Secondly, theres a huge variation on the style bonus, even though the cap stays the same.  if testing on a lvl 0 grey is limiting as many variables as we think, why are the style bonus numbers so different?<br><br>I'm gonna try to get a friend of mine to help me do some extensive testing on a single monster, repeatedly attacking it, but not ever killing it, to see what kind of stuff comes up. <p>Dither Disgustipated<BR>Kobold Shadowblade<BR>Ragnarok, Palomides</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 1:19:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about Amount Spec'd?</span><hr size=1> I think testing on grays is good to find out max. After we find out Max we can start to figure out what Min is, then what Dex, Str, Weapon Condition, Qua, and all those other stats do to change it. <br><br>Start with the easy stuff.<br><br>I think the Style amount represents your actual Roll modified for Level of you and the mob. Then capped off. The reason its so high against level -0- grays is because they are so freaking now. You could do it on level 15 grays if you are level 40 and still see you hit CAP but style numbers would be lower. Eventually when style numbers are low enough (in the very high grays, almost greens) you will stop hitting your cap. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2089.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2089.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2089.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2089.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2089.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br